metadata.name: Dog Eat Dog
metadata.description:
Introducing "Trash Barbie," a thought-provoking post-photography art collection of 200 enigmatic images, reimagining Ken and Barbie as they address themes of neglect, abuse, and objectification.

Venture into the unvarnished world of "Trash Barbie," where images depict dolls marked by time as a metaphor for the vulnerability and resilience of real-life humans. Set against the backdrop of motels, trailer parks, and rural living, each piece exposes raw emotions beneath the surface.

The collection explores intricate relationships and objectification within "Trash Barbie," offering insight into the nuanced power dynamics between individuals. "Trash Barbie" invites introspection and discourse on neglect, abuse, and objectification in society. Embrace its haunting allure and embark on a journey towards understanding and empathy.
